{"name":"Badger","size":"small","type":"humanoid","tag":"goblin","alignment":"chaotic evil","hitDice":"","armorName":"mage armor","shieldBonus":0,"natArmorBonus":7,"otherArmorDesc":"10","speed":"30","burrowSpeed":"0","climbSpeed":"0","flySpeed":"0","hover":false,"swimSpeed":"0","customHP":true,"customSpeed":false,"hpText":"230 (20d8 + 60)","speedDesc":"30 ft.","strPoints":"12","dexPoints":"18","conPoints":"16","intPoints":"12","wisPoints":"16","chaPoints":"22","blindsight":"0","blind":false,"darkvision":"0","tremorsense":"0","truesight":"30","telepathy":60,"cr":"22","customCr":"1 (200 XP)","customProf":2,"isLegendary":true,"legendariesDescription":"The monster can take 3 legendary actions, choosing from the options below. Only one legendary action option can be used at a time and only at the end of another creature's turn. The monster regains spent legendary actions at the start of its turn.","isLair":false,"lairDescription":"When fighting inside its lair, the monster can invoke the ambient magic to take lair actions. On initiative count 20 (losing initiative ties), the monster can take one lair action to cause one of the following effects:","lairDescriptionEnd":"The monster can't repeat an effect until they have all been used, and it can't use the same effect two rounds in a row.","isMythic":true,"mythicDescription":"If the monster's mythic trait is active, it can use the options below as actions / legendary actions for 1 hour after using Form of Hatred.","isRegional":false,"regionalDescription":"The region containing the monster's lair is warped by the creature's presence, which creates one or more of the following effects:","regionalDescriptionEnd":"If the monster dies, the first two effects fade over the course of 3d10 days.","properties":[],"abilities":[{"name":"Form of Hatred","desc":"When Badger is reduced to 0 hit points, his Form of Hatred activates as his body becomes unstable and he absorbs the souls of his remaining warlocks. Badger regains 230 hit points, replenishes all of his spells, and can now use his Mythic Actions."},{"name":"Legendary Resistance (3/day)","desc":"If [MON] fails a saving throw, it can choose to succeed instead."},{"name":"Alert","desc":"Badger gains a +5 bonus to initiative. He also can't be surprised while he is conscious, and other creatures don't gain advantage on attack rolls against him as a result of being unseen by him."},{"name":"Indescribable Form","desc":"Badger's form is no longer bound by the laws of reality. As an action, you can choose to appear as any creature or object that is Small or Medium, such as a dog, a mass of floating lights, an idealized version of yourself, or a simple wooden crate. No matter what appearance you chose, your statistics and capacity for action are the same. This appearance is a physical change, but magic that allows others to discern the true form of shapeshifters will reveal your normal appearance. This appearance lasts until you choose to change it again."},{"name":"Innate Spellcasting","desc":"Badger's innate spellcasting ability is Charisma (spell save DC [CHA SAVE], [CHA ATK] to hit with spell attacks). It can innately cast the following spells, requiring no material components:\n\n> At will: _arcane eye, detect magic, detect thoughts, invisibility, levitate, mage armor, silent image, speak with animals, speak with dead_\n> Once per day (each): _Hold Monster, Mass Suggestion, Finger of Death, Feeblemind, Asmodeus' Eternal Suffering, Imprisonment"},{"name":"War Caster","desc":"Badger has advantage on Constitution saving throws that he makes to maintain concentration on a spell when he takes damage. He can cast when having his hands occupied. He can cast spells for opportunity attacks, as long as the spell has a casting time of 1 action."},{"name":"Dark One's Blessing","desc":"When Badger reduces a hostile creature to 0 hit points, he gains 25 hp."}],"actions":[{"name":"Eldritch Annihilation","desc":"_Ranged Spell Attack:_ Five beams of eldritch energy streak towards creatures within range. [CHA ATK] to hit, range 300 ft., one target. _Hit:_ [CHA 1D10] force damage per beam. Badger can allow each beam to do one of the following:\n- Move the creature hit up to 10 feet closer to him.\n- Push the creature hit up to 10 feet away from him.\n- Reduce the hit creature's speed by 10 feet until the end of your next turn.\n- Damage a secondary target within 5 feet of the primary target, at the expense of 1d4 hit points.\n- Cast fireball as a bonus action centered on the creature hit.\n\nBadger can also expend a bonus action before casting to empower the eldritch annihilation with the following:\n**Doom**: Channel all energy into one location. Target only one creature that must succeed on a DC [CHA SAVE] Charisma saving throw or be struck by all beams. If the attack kills the creature, Badger can empower his next Eldritch Annihilation to be Doom.\n**Destruction**: Unleash a web of eldritch energy. Target one creature and up to six other creatures within 30 feet of the primary target. Each secondary target must succeed a DC [CHA SAVE] Wisdom saving throw or be struck by the one beam of the blast. The primary target is struck by a number of beams equal to the number of creatures who failed their saving throw."},{"name":"Painful Infiltration (Form of Hated)","desc":"Badger's loose form attempts to force itself into the orifices of a target. The target must make a DC [CHA SAVE] Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, Badger infects the body for 1d4 amount of turns. While Badger is infecting the body, the target gains three levels of exhaustion, and takes 8d10 necrotic damage at the start of each of its turns that Badger is infecting their body. At the start of each turn, the target may make a Constitution saving throw to exalt Badger from their body. If the target is attacked from a source other than Badger, Badger is dealt the same amount of damage and the target may make another Constitution saving throw. If the target is killed from the damage Badger inflicts from this ability, their body is destroyed and Badger's body reconstitutes in the target's location. If the target is killed from another source, Badger is removed from the body."}],"bonusActions":[{"name":"Nimble Escape","desc":"[MON] can take the Disengage or Hide action as a bonus action on each of its turns."}],"reactions":[],"legendaries":[{"name":"Eldritch Blast","desc":"_Ranged Spell Attack:_ One beam of eldritch energy streaks towards a creature within range. [CHA ATK] to hit, range 300 ft., one target. _Hit:_ [CHA 1D10] force damage."},{"name":"Hurl Through Hell (3 Actions)","desc":"Badger can attack ([DEX ATK] to hit) a creature within a range of 5 ft. If the attack hits, he instantly transports them to the nine hells. At the end of his next turn, the target returns to the space it previously occupied, and if it is not a fiend, takes 10d10 psychic damage."}],"mythics":[{"name":"Indescribable Form","desc":"Badger uses his indescribable form action."},{"name":"Teleport","desc":"Badger's form dissipates and reconstitutes in an unoccupied space within 120 feet."}],"lairs":[],"regionals":[],"sthrows":[{"name":"wis","order":4},{"name":"cha","order":5}],"skills":[{"name":"arcana","stat":"int"},{"name":"deception","stat":"cha","note":" (ex)"},{"name":"insight","stat":"wis"},{"name":"intimidation","stat":"cha"},{"name":"perception","stat":"wis"},{"name":"performance","stat":"cha"},{"name":"persuasion","stat":"cha"},{"name":"stealth","stat":"dex","note":" (ex)"},{"name":"survival","stat":"wis"}],"damagetypes":[{"name":"acid","note":" (Resistant)","type":"r"},{"name":"fire","note":" (Resistant)","type":"r"},{"name":"psychic","note":" (Resistant)","type":"r"}],"specialdamage":[],"conditions":[],"languages":[{"name":"Abyssal","speaks":true},{"name":"Goblin","speaks":true},{"name":"Infernal","speaks":true}],"understandsBut":"","shortName":"Badger","pluralName":"","doubleColumns":true,"separationPoint":7,"damage":[]}